 ratio.", "bbox": [112.5, 1119.7, 1167.8, 1148.1]}, {"text": "RAILWAY OPERATING REVENUES -- NS' total railway operating revenues were $9.4 billion in 2006.  See", "bbox": [112.5, 1175.5, 1154.2, 1200.8]}, {"text": "the financial information by traffic segment in Part II, Item 7, “Management’s Discussion and Analysis of", "bbox": [112.5, 1201.7, 1090.2, 1227.1]}, {"text": "Financial Condition and Results of Operations.”", "bbox": [112.5, 1228.1, 559.9, 1253.4]}, {"text": "COAL TRAFFIC -- Coal, coke and iron ore -- most of which is bituminous coal -- is NS' railroads' largest", "bbox": [112.5, 1280.9, 1102.9, 1306.2]}, {"text": "commodity group as measured by revenues.  The railroads handled a total of 190.6 million tons in 2006, most of", "bbox": [112.5, 1307.2, 1149.5, 1332.6]}, {"text": "which originated on NS' lines in West Virginia, Virginia, Pennsylvania and Kentucky.  Revenues from coal, coke", "bbox": [112.5, 1333.6, 1158.6, 1358.9]}, {"text": "and iron ore accounted for about 25% of NS' total railway operating revenues in 2006.", "bbox": [112.5, 1359.9, 909.7, 1385.2]}, {"text": "Total coal handled through all system ports in 2006 was 33.8 million tons.  Of this total, 10.8 million tons", "bbox": [112.5, 1412.6, 1087.6, 1437.9]}, {"text": "(including coastwise traffic) moved through Norfolk, Virginia, 2.4 million tons moved through the Baltimore", "bbox": [112.5, 1439.0, 1119.9, 1464.3]}, {"text": "Terminal, 13.0 million tons moved to various docks on the Ohio River, and 7.6 million tons moved to various", "bbox": [112.5, 1465.4, 1124.1, 1490.7]}]}